===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[prepare]]
#: {{zh-x|備而不用|to have something ready just in case; to keep something for possible future use}}
#* {{zh-x|孔明 索 紙筆，屏退 左右，密 書 十六 字 曰：「欲 破 ^曹 公，宜 用 火攻；萬事 俱 備，只 欠 東風。」|Kongming asked for papers and pen, dismissed the attendants, then secretly wrote sixteen words: "To defeat Lord Cao, must use fire attack; everything is '''ready''', only missing the easternly wind."|ref=Sanguo Yanyi}}
# to [[provide]] or [[prepare]] against; to [[take]] [[precaution]]s [[against]]
#: {{zh-x|攻其不備|to attack when the enemy is unprepared}}
#: {{zh-co|以 備 不時之需|for unexpected future use}}
#* {{zh-x|君子 曰：「不備 不虞，不可以 師。」|The gentleman said: "One who is not '''prepared against''' the unexpected cannot command troops."|ref=Zuozhuan}}
#* {{zh-x|將 兵 北屯 ^下曲陽，備 ^匈奴。|({{w|Ma Wu}}) led his troops, whom he stationed north – at Xiaquyang – '''to defend against''' the Xiongnu.|ref=Houhanshu}}
# [[equipment]]
#: {{zh-x|軍備|armament; arms}}
# to [[possess]]
#: {{zh-x|才德兼備|to possess both ability and integrity}}
# [[complete]]
#* {{zh-x|居 惡{wū} 在。仁 是 也。路 惡{wū} 在。義 是 也。居-仁 由-義、大人 之 事-備 矣。|Wherever you dwell, make it Humane; whatever course you travel, make it Just. Abiding in humaneness and acting through fairness—this is how the great man '''completes''' his work|ref=Mengzi}}
#* {{zh-x|周-公 謂 ^魯-公 曰：「君子 不 施{chí} 其 親，不 使 大臣 怨 乎 不 以。故舊，無 大-故，則 不 棄 也。無 求 備 於 一人。」|The {{w|Duke of Zhou}} said to {{w|Bo Qin|Duke of Lu}}: "The gentleman does not neglect his kinsmen, does not make the great ministers grudge over being not used, and certainly does not reject old friends without great causes. Neither does he not seek '''perfection''' in one man."|ref=Lunyu}}
# [[fully]]
#: {{zh-co|備 受 關注|to attract a lot of attention}}
#* {{zh-x|乃 命 冢宰，農事 備 收。|Orders are also given to the chief minister, after the fruits of husbandry have all been gathered in, […]|ref=Liji}}

